Meet <b>Tannah</b>, our Citizen of the Week!<br><br>Tannah just moved to Millsberry, on June 26, 2007, and is now happily living at <a href='/home/?user=mscatlady1'>44542-B Wild Rose Road</a> in Ravenwood. She likes hiking and taking long walks, and has already seen most of the city this way.  <br><br>Since arriving here over the summer, Tannah has done a lot! She set up a yard sale and offers reasonable prices. She also has quite a few trophies, and is getting to know all the games in the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/complex/arcade.phtml">arcade </a>. The summer was pretty hot this year, so she spent time at the pool and in the shade of the trees in her backyard. She has some pets around too, and they make great company.<br><br>Tannah has quickly become a star artist in <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/museum/paint/">Millsberry's art class </a>. She is very creative and comes up with ideas that many people have never considered. She often uses her favorites colors (gold, pink, and orange) when she's drawing in her sketchbook, but when she paints she prefers a different color palette.  <br><br>This fall, she is hoping to get to know Millsberry even better, add to her home, and have fun with her friends. With school starting, she's sure to meet many new people and win them over. Look for her around town!<br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Tannah, and and congrats on being named Millsberry's Citizen of the Week!<br></div>
